article.description: — Caleb Fields' 22 points helped Arkansas State defeat UL Monroe 95-80 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Arkansas State defeats UL Monroe 95-80
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- — Caleb Fields' 22 points helped Arkansas State defeat UL Monroe 95-80 on Saturday night. Fields also had 13 assists for the Red Wolves (10-13, 6-5 Sun Belt Conference). Izaiyah Nelson scored 16 points and added 10 rebounds and four blocks. Zane Butler was 4 of 5 shooting, including 3 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 5 from the line to finish with 16 points. The Warhawks (7-14, 3-8) were led by Nika Metskhvarishvili, who posted 20 points. UL Monroe also got 19 points and three steals from Tyreese Watson. Tyreke Locure also had 11 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
